cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR 

The paper deals with defending against adversarial examples in biometric applications, specifically iris recognition. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and cybersecurity and privacy (cs.CR) sub-categories. The proposed defense strategies are based on wavelet domain denoising, which involves manipulating and analyzing the input data at a granular level, indicating a possible connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper focuses on iris recognition, which is a subfield of image recognition (cs.IR).
